SIMPLE: sorrowful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sorrowful
<hw>Sor"row*ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sorweful</ets>, AS. <ets>sorgful</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Full of sorrow; exhibiting sorrow; sad; dejected; distressed.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧This <xex>sorrowful</xex> prisoner.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My soul is exceeding <qex>sorrowful</qex>, even unto death.</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. xxvi. 38.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Producing sorrow; exciting grief; mournful;
lamentable; grievous; <as>as, a <ex>sorrowful</ex>
accident</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sad; mournful; dismal; disconsolate; drear;
dreary; grievous; lamentable; doleful; distressing.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sor"row*ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sor"row*ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sorrowless</ent>⟦br⟧
